    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf you right click in a buffer and then right click inside of the opened context menu when using a gui that supports multigrid, neovim will request that the window for the context menu be anchored to itself which is incorrect.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. open nvim in a multigrid gui. I can reproduce this in default neovide\r\n2. Move the mouse (otherwise the next step won't show a context menu at all, presumably related to the above issue).\r\n3. Right click somewhere (not hold) to show the Paste/Select All/etc context menu.\r\n4. Move the mouse to inside the context menu, then click and hold the right mouse button.\r\n\r\nAt this point neovim will request a recursive floating window anchor. In current neovide stable this crashes but a fix is in progress to ignore this invalid request. However neovim shouldn't send a request like that in the first place.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI think ideally the second right click should be ignored.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nneovide\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nn/a\n\n### Installation\n\ndownloaded from releases",
